<item>
            <title>[FELIX-628] Architecture service should not publish the instance.name property</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-628</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Architecture service is published with the instance.name property. However, this property should be use only by &quot;functional&quot; interfaces. So, this property name should be change in &quot;architecture.instance&quot;. This allows discovering all services provided by an instance (without interfering with the Architecture service). The property value stills the instance name.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
